Parkinson's disease is known to pose a significant burden on society in 
industrialized countries. However, few studies have been conducted in Italy 
using administrative healthcare databases for epidemiological purposes. We 
wanted to estimate the incidence and prevalence rates of Parkinson's disease in 
the Italian region of Umbria by means of linkage between several sources of 
administrative healthcare data: hospitalization episodes, exemptions from 
medical charges, drug prescriptions from general practitioners and physicians 
